            "content": "# Submit API Bundle Format — Implementation Plan\n\n> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Migrate `POST /api/v1/submit` from single base64-encoded WirePayload to binary bundle format with per-frame results.\n\n**Architecture:** Add bundle body encode/parse helpers to `reme-bundle`. Rewrite the node submit handler to accept binary bundles, move per-IP rate limiting inline (N tokens for N frames), and restructure the response as `{ results: [...] }`. Update all transport clients (`HttpTarget`, `HttpTransport`) to encode requests as count=1 bundles and parse the new response. Update replication to use raw bytes instead of base64 strings. Update embedded node handler similarly. Fix all 39 affected tests.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Rust, Axum, tower_governor, reqwest, SQLite, postcard\n\n**Spec:** `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-03-27-submit-api-bundle-format.md`\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\ncrates/reme-bundle/src/\n├── lib.rs              # Add pub mod body; re-export encode_body, parse_body\n└── body.rs             # NEW: bundle body encode/parse (no magic/version/checksum)\n\ncrates/reme-transport/src/\n├── http_target.rs      # Modify: submit_payload encoding + SubmitResponse restructure\n└── http.rs             # Modify: submit_to_node encoding + SubmitResponse restructure\n\ncrates/reme-node-core/src/\n└── mailbox_store.rs    # Modify: add enqueue_batch to trait + impl\n\napps/node/src/\n├── api.rs              # Modify: submit_payload handler rewrite, new response types, inline rate limiting\n├── config.rs           # Modify: add max_body_size, max_batch_size fields\n├── rate_limit.rs       # Modify: expose submit_ip limiter for inline use\n└── replication.rs      # Modify: replicate_payload takes Vec<u8> instead of String\n\napps/client/src/tui/\n└── http_server.rs      # Modify: submit_handler binary format, batch support\n\nCargo.toml (workspace)  # No change needed — reme-bundle already in workspace deps\n\nTests (modify all):\n├── apps/node/tests/receipt_on_submit.rs        # 5 tests\n├── apps/node/tests/signed_replication.rs       # 3 tests\n├── crates/reme-core/tests/integration.rs       # 19 tests (via transport change)\n├── crates/reme-transport/tests/http_auth_test.rs # 5 tests (response shape)\n└── apps/client/src/tui/http_server.rs          # 7 inline tests\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Bundle body encode/parse helpers\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `crates/reme-bundle/src/body.rs`\n- Modify: `crates/reme-bundle/src/lib.rs`\n\nThese helpers encode/parse the HTTP submit body format: `[count: u32 LE][frame_len: u32 LE][frame]...` — same framing as the `.reme` file format but without the file-level header (magic, version, checksum).\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write tests for `encode_body` and `parse_body`**\n\nCreate `crates/reme-bundle/src/body.rs` with tests at the bottom:\n\n```rust\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::*;\n\n    #[test]\n    fn round_trip_single_frame() {\n        let encoded = encode_body(&[b\"hello\"]);\n        let frames = parse_body(&encoded, 100).unwrap();\n        assert_eq!(frames.len(), 1);\n        assert_eq!(frames[0], b\"hello\");\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn round_trip_multiple_frames() {\n        let encoded = encode_body(&[b\"aaa\", b\"bbb\", b\"ccc\"]);\n        let frames = parse_body(&encoded, 100).unwrap();\n        assert_eq!(frames.len(), 3);\n        assert_eq!(frames[0], b\"aaa\");\n        assert_eq!(frames[1], b\"bbb\");\n        assert_eq!(frames[2], b\"ccc\");\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn round_trip_empty_frame() {\n        let encoded = encode_body(&[b\"\"]);\n        let frames = parse_body(&encoded, 100).unwrap();\n        assert_eq!(frames.len(), 1);\n        assert_eq!(frames[0], b\"\");\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn parse_empty_body_fails() {\n        assert!(parse_body(b\"\", 100).is_err());\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn parse_zero_count_fails() {\n        let body = 0_u32.to_le_bytes();\n        assert!(parse_body(&body, 100).is_err());\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn parse_exceeds_max_frames() {\n        let encoded = encode_body(&[b\"a\", b\"b\", b\"c\"]);\n        let err = parse_body(&encoded, 2).unwrap_err();\n        assert!(matches!(err, BodyParseError::TooManyFrames { .. }));\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn parse_truncated_body() {\n        let encoded = encode_body(&[b\"hello\"]);\n        let truncated = &encoded[..6]; // cut mid-frame\n        assert!(parse_body(truncated, 100).is_err());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Implement `encode_body` and `parse_body`**\n\n```rust\n//! Bundle body encoding for HTTP submit API.\n//!\n//! Wire format: `[count: u32 LE][frame_len: u32 LE][frame bytes]...`\n//! Same framing as the `.reme` file format but without the file-level\n//! header (magic, version, flags, checksum).\n\n/// Errors from parsing a bundle body.\n#[derive(Debug, thiserror::Error)]\n#[non_exhaustive]\npub enum BodyParseError {\n    #[error(\"body too short: need at least 4 bytes for frame count\")]\n    TooShort,\n\n    #[error(\"frame count is zero\")]\n    EmptyBundle,\n\n    #[error(\"too many frames: {count} exceeds max {max}\")]\n    TooManyFrames { count: u32, max: u32 },\n\n    #[error(\"truncated: frame {index} declares {declared} bytes but only {available} remain\")]\n    Truncated {\n        index: u32,\n        declared: u32,\n        available: usize,\n    },\n}\n\n/// Encode frames into the bundle body wire format.\n///\n/// Produces `[count: u32 LE][frame_len: u32 LE][frame]...`\npub fn encode_body(frames: &[&[u8]]) -> Vec<u8> {\n    let total_size = 4 + frames.iter().map(|f| 4 + f.len()).sum::<usize>();\n    let mut buf = Vec::with_capacity(total_size);\n\n    #[allow(clippy::cast_possible_truncation)]\n    let count = frames.len() as u32;\n    buf.extend_from_slice(&count.to_le_bytes());\n\n    for frame in frames {\n        #[allow(clippy::cast_possible_truncation)]\n        let len = frame.len() as u32;\n        buf.extend_from_slice(&len.to_le_bytes());\n        buf.extend_from_slice(frame);\n    }\n\n    buf\n}\n\n/// Parse a bundle body into individual frames.\n///\n/// Returns an error if the body is malformed, empty, or exceeds `max_frames`.\npub fn parse_body(bytes: &[u8], max_frames: u32) -> Result<Vec<Vec<u8>>, BodyParseError> {\n    if bytes.len() < 4 {\n        return Err(BodyParseError::TooShort);\n    }\n\n    let count = u32::from_le_bytes([bytes[0], bytes[1], bytes[2], bytes[3]]);\n    if count == 0 {\n        return Err(BodyParseError::EmptyBundle);\n    }\n    if count > max_frames {\n        return Err(BodyParseError::TooManyFrames { count, max: max_frames });\n    }\n\n    let mut offset = 4;\n    let mut frames = Vec::with_capacity(count as usize);\n\n    for i in 0..count {\n        if offset + 4 > bytes.len() {\n            return Err(BodyParseError::Truncated {\n                index: i,\n                declared: 0,\n                available: bytes.len().saturating_sub(offset),\n            });\n        }\n        let frame_len = u32::from_le_bytes([\n            bytes[offset], bytes[offset + 1], bytes[offset + 2], bytes[offset + 3],\n        ]);\n        offset += 4;\n\n        let frame_len_usize = frame_len as usize;\n        if offset + frame_len_usize > bytes.len() {\n            return Err(BodyParseError::Truncated {\n                index: i,\n                declared: frame_len,\n                available: bytes.len().saturating_sub(offset),\n            });\n        }\n        frames.push(bytes[offset..offset + frame_len_usize].to_vec());\n        offset += frame_len_usize;\n    }\n\n    Ok(frames)\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Add module to lib.rs**\n\nIn `crates/reme-bundle/src/lib.rs`, add:\n```rust\npub mod body;\npub use body::{encode_body, parse_body, BodyParseError};\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run tests**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p reme-bundle`\nExpected: All existing tests + 7 new body tests pass.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```\nfeat(bundle): add bundle body encode/parse helpers for HTTP submit API\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Node config changes\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `apps/node/src/config.rs`\n- Modify: `apps/node/src/api.rs` (constant → config field)\n\nAdd `max_body_size` and `max_batch_size` to the node config. Replace the hardcoded `MAX_BODY_SIZE` constant.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add fields to `ServerConfig`**\n\nIn `apps/node/src/config.rs`, find the `ServerConfig` struct (or whichever struct holds server-level config) and add:\n\n```rust\n#[derivative(Default(value = \"2_097_152\"))]\npub max_body_size: usize,\n\n#[derivative(Default(value = \"100\"))]\npub max_batch_size: u32,\n```\n\nAdd corresponding CLI args if the pattern exists.\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Replace hardcoded `MAX_BODY_SIZE` in `api.rs`**\n\nRemove the `const MAX_BODY_SIZE: usize = 256 * 1024;` constant. Read `max_body_size` from `AppState` config and apply it in `router()`. The `DefaultBodyLimit::max()` layer needs the value at router construction time — pass it as a parameter.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Verify compilation**\n\nRun: `cargo check --all-targets`\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Commit**\n\n```\nfeat(node): add configurable max_body_size and max_batch_size\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Node API handler rewrite + response types + rate limiting\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `apps/node/src/api.rs` (major rewrite of `submit_payload`, new response types, inline rate limiting)\n- Modify: `apps/node/src/rate_limit.rs` (expose submit_ip limiter for inline use)\n- Modify: `apps/node/Cargo.toml` (add `reme-bundle` dependency)\n\nThis is the largest task. The submit handler changes from base64 single-payload to binary bundle with per-frame results.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add `reme-bundle` dependency to `apps/node/Cargo.toml`**\n\n```toml\nreme-bundle = { workspace = true }\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Define new response types**\n\nReplace the existing `SubmitResponse` in `api.rs` with:\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Debug, Serialize)]\nstruct SubmitResponse {\n    results: Vec<FrameResult>,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Serialize)]\nstruct FrameResult {\n    status: &'static str,\n    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = \"Option::is_none\")]\n    ack_secret: Option<String>,\n    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = \"Option::is_none\")]\n    signature: Option<String>,\n    #[serde(skip_serializing_if = \"Option::is_none\")]\n    error: Option<String>,\n}\n\nimpl FrameResult {\n    fn ok(ack_secret: Option<String>, signature: Option<String>) -> Self {\n        Self { status: \"ok\", ack_secret, signature, error: None }\n    }\n\n    fn error(msg: impl Into<String>) -> Self {\n        Self { status: \"error\", ack_secret: None, signature: None, error: Some(msg.into()) }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Expose per-IP rate limiter for inline use**\n\nIn `apps/node/src/rate_limit.rs`:\n- Remove `apply_submit_ip` (no longer used as middleware)\n- Add a public method to get the raw governor config or limiter so the handler can call `check_key`/`check` inline\n- The handler will consume N tokens for N frames\n\nIn `api.rs` router setup: remove the `limiters.apply_submit_ip(submit_route)` middleware call. The submit route no longer has IP rate limiting as middleware.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Rewrite `submit_payload` handler**\n\nThe new handler:\n1. Takes `body: Bytes` (raw binary, no base64)\n2. Calls `reme_bundle::parse_body(&body, state.config.max_batch_size)`\n3. Checks per-IP rate limit inline: consume `frame_count` tokens\n4. For each frame: `WirePayload::decode` → dispatch to `handle_message` or tombstone path\n5. Collects `Vec<FrameResult>`\n6. Returns `Json(SubmitResponse { results })`\n\nThe existing `handle_message` function needs to be refactored from returning `axum::response::Response` to returning a `FrameResult` (or a structured type that the handler aggregates). Currently it returns HTTP responses directly with status codes — extract the logic into a function that returns `Result<FrameResult, FrameResult>` or similar.\n\nKey changes to `handle_message`:\n- Remove `payload_b64: String` parameter (no longer base64)\n- Add `wire_payload_bytes: Vec<u8>` parameter (raw frame bytes for replication)\n- Return `FrameResult` instead of `axum::response::Response`\n- The caller (submit_payload) builds the HTTP response\n\nSimilarly for the tombstone handling path.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Update replication call**\n\nIn the rewritten handler, call `replicate_payload` with raw bytes instead of base64 string. See Task 4 for the replication change.\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Verify the node compiles**\n\nRun: `cargo check -p node`\nExpected: Compiles (tests may not pass yet — transport clients still send old format).\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Commit**\n\n```\nfeat(node): rewrite submit API to accept binary bundle format\n\n- Accept application/vnd.reme.bundle content type\n- Parse bundle body (count + length-prefixed frames)\n- Per-frame results in response: { results: [{ status, ack_secret?, signature?, error? }] }\n- Move per-IP rate limiting inline (N tokens for N frames)\n- Best-effort processing: partial batch success supported\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Replication format change\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `apps/node/src/replication.rs`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Change `replicate_payload` signature**\n\nFrom: `pub fn replicate_payload(self: &Arc<Self>, payload_b64: String, from_node: Option<String>)`\nTo: `pub fn replicate_payload(self: &Arc<Self>, wire_payload_bytes: Vec<u8>, from_node: Option<String>)`\n\nInside: re-encode as a count=1 bundle body using `reme_bundle::encode_body(&[&wire_payload_bytes])`. Send as `application/vnd.reme.bundle` with raw bytes (no base64). Sign the new binary body.\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Update Content-Type header**\n\nChange `.header(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain\")` to `.header(\"Content-Type\", \"application/vnd.reme.bundle\")`.\n\nChange `.body(payload_b64.clone())` to `.body(bundle_body.clone())` where `bundle_body` is the encoded bytes.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Update signing**\n\nThe signing call `SignedHeaders::sign(identity, \"POST\", path, payload_b64.as_bytes(), dest)` changes to sign the binary bundle body bytes instead.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Add reme-bundle dep if not already**\n\nAlready added in Task 3 for `apps/node`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Verify compilation**\n\nRun: `cargo check -p node`\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```\nrefactor(replication): use binary bundle format for node-to-node replication\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Transport client update (HttpTarget + HttpTransport)\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `crates/reme-transport/src/http_target.rs`\n- Modify: `crates/reme-transport/src/http.rs`\n- Modify: `crates/reme-transport/Cargo.toml` (add `reme-bundle` dependency)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add `reme-bundle` dep to `reme-transport`**\n\nIn `crates/reme-transport/Cargo.toml`:\n```toml\nreme-bundle = { workspace = true }\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Update `SubmitResponse` in `http_target.rs`**\n\nReplace the existing private `SubmitResponse` struct (lines 147-157) with the new shape:\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Debug, Deserialize)]\nstruct SubmitResponse {\n    results: Vec<FrameResult>,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Deserialize)]\nstruct FrameResult {\n    #[allow(dead_code)]\n    status: String,\n    ack_secret: Option<String>,\n    signature: Option<String>,\n    #[allow(dead_code)]\n    error: Option<String>,\n}\n```\n\nUpdate `into_raw_receipt` to work on `FrameResult` instead.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Rewrite `submit_payload` in `HttpTarget`**\n\nChange encoding from base64 to binary bundle:\n```rust\nlet wire_bytes = wire_payload.encode().map_err(|e| TransportError::Serialization(e.to_string()))?;\nlet body = reme_bundle::encode_body(&[&wire_bytes]);\n```\n\nChange Content-Type to `application/vnd.reme.bundle`. Send `body` as raw bytes.\n\nChange response parsing to extract `results[0]`:\n```rust\nlet response: SubmitResponse = resp.json().await...;\nlet frame_result = response.results.into_iter().next()\n    .ok_or_else(|| TransportError::ServerError(\"empty results array\".to_string()))?;\nOk(frame_result.into_raw_receipt())\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Update `SubmitResponse` in legacy `http.rs`**\n\nThe legacy `HttpTransport::submit_to_node` uses its own `SubmitResponse` struct (lines 53-57 in http.rs). Update it to match the new shape. The result is discarded (`_result`), so the change is just deserialization compatibility.\n\nUpdate `submit_to_node` encoding to use binary bundle format, same as HttpTarget.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Verify compilation**\n\nRun: `cargo check -p reme-transport`\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```\nfeat(transport): encode submit requests as binary bundles\n\n- HttpTarget: encode as count=1 bundle, parse new response shape\n- HttpTransport: same encoding change for legacy multi-URL transport\n- Content-Type: application/vnd.reme.bundle\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Embedded node update\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `apps/client/src/tui/http_server.rs`\n- Modify: `apps/client/Cargo.toml` (add `reme-bundle` dependency if not present)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add `reme-bundle` dep to client**\n\nCheck if already present. If not:\n```toml\nreme-bundle = { workspace = true }\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Update embedded `SubmitResponse`**\n\nReplace the `SubmitResponse` struct in `http_server.rs` with the same shape as the node:\n```rust\n#[derive(Debug, Serialize)]\nstruct SubmitResponse {\n    results: Vec<FrameResult>,\n}\n// ... same FrameResult as node\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Rewrite `submit_handler`**\n\nChange from base64 string parsing to binary bundle parsing:\n1. Take `body: Bytes` instead of `body: String`\n2. Parse with `reme_bundle::parse_body(&body, 10)` (max 10 frames)\n3. Loop through frames, processing each:\n   - `WirePayload::decode` → dispatch\n   - Tombstone frames → per-frame error (not request-level 400)\n   - Wrong routing key → per-frame error\n   - Duplicate → per-frame ok (no receipt)\n   - Success → generate receipt, store, per-frame ok with receipt\n4. Collect `Vec<FrameResult>`, return `SubmitResponse { results }`\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Update body size limit**\n\nChange `RequestBodyLimitLayer::new(256 * 1024)` to `RequestBodyLimitLayer::new(512 * 1024)`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Verify compilation**\n\nRun: `cargo check -p client`\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```\nfeat(client): update embedded node to accept binary bundle format\n\n- Parse application/vnd.reme.bundle body\n- Allow batches up to 10 frames\n- Per-frame error handling for tombstones and routing key mismatches\n- Increase body limit to 512 KiB\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Fix existing tests + add new tests\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `apps/node/tests/receipt_on_submit.rs` (5 tests)\n- Modify: `apps/node/tests/signed_replication.rs` (3 tests)\n- Modify: `crates/reme-core/tests/integration.rs` (19 tests — should auto-fix via transport change)\n- Modify: `crates/reme-transport/tests/http_auth_test.rs` (5 tests)\n- Modify: `apps/client/src/tui/http_server.rs` inline tests (7 tests)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Fix `receipt_on_submit.rs` tests**\n\nThe `submit_envelope` helper (line 141) must change from:\n```rust\nlet body = BASE64_STANDARD.encode(wire_payload.encode().unwrap());\n// POST as text/plain\n```\nTo:\n```rust\nlet wire_bytes = wire_payload.encode().unwrap();\nlet body = reme_bundle::encode_body(&[&wire_bytes]);\n// POST as application/vnd.reme.bundle with raw bytes\n```\n\nThe local `SubmitResponse` struct (line 19) must change to `{ results: Vec<FrameResult> }`. Tests extract `results[0]` for receipt assertions.\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Fix `signed_replication.rs` tests**\n\nSame encoding change for any direct HTTP POST calls. Replication tests verify that signed payloads are accepted by peer nodes — the signature now signs binary bundle bytes.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Verify integration tests pass**\n\nThe 19 tests in `crates/reme-core/tests/integration.rs` go through `HttpTarget::submit_message` which was updated in Task 5. They should pass without test-level changes since the transport layer handles encoding.\n\nRun: `cargo test -p reme-core --test integration`\n\nIf any fail, investigate and fix.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Fix `http_auth_test.rs` wiremock tests**\n\nThe mock server responses return `{\"status\":\"ok\"}`. Update to return `{\"results\":[{\"status\":\"ok\"}]}` so `SubmitResponse` deserialization succeeds.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Fix embedded node inline tests (7 tests)**\n\nSame pattern as receipt tests: change body encoding from base64 to binary bundle. Update response assertions to use `results[0]`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Add new integration tests**\n\nAdd to `apps/node/tests/` (or extend existing test file):\n\n1. **Batch submit test**: Submit 10 messages in one request, verify all stored and fetchable.\n2. **Partial success test**: Submit batch with a duplicate message, verify `results` array has mix of ok/error.\n3. **Embedded node batch test**: Submit 3 messages to embedded node, verify all processed.\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Run full test suite**\n\nRun: `cargo test --workspace --all-features --all-targets`\nExpected: All tests pass.\n\n- [ ] **Step 8: Commit**\n\n```\ntest: update all tests for binary bundle submit format\n\n- Fix 5 receipt_on_submit tests\n- Fix 3 signed_replication tests\n- Fix 5 http_auth_test wiremock mocks\n- Fix 7 embedded node inline tests\n- Add batch submit integration tests\n- 19 integration tests pass via transport layer change\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: MailboxStore::enqueue_batch\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `crates/reme-node-core/src/mailbox_store.rs`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add `enqueue_batch` to trait**\n\n```rust\nfn enqueue_batch(\n    &self,\n    messages: &[(RoutingKey, OuterEnvelope)],\n) -> Result<Vec<Result<(), NodeError>>, NodeError>;\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Implement for `PersistentMailboxStore`**\n\nWrap multiple inserts in a single SQLite transaction. For each message, run the same logic as `enqueue` (expiry cleanup, mailbox limit check, insert). Collect per-message `Result<(), NodeError>`. If the transaction itself fails, return outer `Err`.\n\nDefault implementation on the trait: loop calling `enqueue` for each message (so `InMemoryMailboxStore` or test impls get batch support for free).\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Add tests**\n\nTest batch of 5 messages: all succeed. Test batch where one hits mailbox limit: others still succeed.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Commit**\n\n```\nfeat(node-core): add enqueue_batch to MailboxStore trait\n```\n\nNote: The node handler may or may not use `enqueue_batch` in v1 — it can also loop `enqueue` per-frame. The batch method is an optimization for future use. Wire it in if the handler naturally benefits from it; otherwise leave it available for later.\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Lint + final verification\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: `cargo fmt --all -- --check`**\n- [ ] **Step 2: `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`**\n- [ ] **Step 3: `cargo test --workspace --all-features --all-targets`**\n- [ ] **Step 4: Fix any issues found**\n- [ ] **Step 5: Final commit if needed**\n\n---\n\n## Task Dependency Graph\n\n```\nTask 1 (bundle body helpers) ──┬──→ Task 3 (node handler) ──→ Task 4 (replication)\n                               ├──→ Task 5 (transport client)\n                               ├──→ Task 6 (embedded node)\n                               └──→ Task 7 (tests) ──→ Task 9 (lint)\nTask 2 (config) ───────────────┘\nTask 8 (enqueue_batch) ────────── independent, can be done anytime\n```\n\nTasks 3, 4, 5, 6 can be done in any order but all must be done before Task 7 (tests).\n",
