            "content": "# `reme export` CLI Subcommand — Design Spec\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-28\n**Issue:** #157\n**Milestone:** v0.5 — Sneakernet Export\n\n---\n\n## Goal\n\nExport pending outbox messages to a `.reme` bundle file for sneakernet transfer.\n\n## CLI Interface\n\n```\nreme export [OPTIONS] <FILE>\n\nArguments:\n  <FILE>              Output path for the .reme bundle\n\nOptions:\n  --to <PUBLIC_ID>    Export only messages for this recipient (base64)\n  --all               Export all pending outbox messages (default)\n  --include-sent      Include already-confirmed messages\n  --force             Overwrite existing file\n  --limit <N>         Export at most N messages\n  --since <DURATION>  Only messages created within this duration (e.g. 24h, 7d)\n```\n\n`--to` and `--all` are mutually exclusive. `--all` is the default when neither is specified.\n\n`--since` accepts `humantime`-compatible relative durations: `30m`, `24h`, `7d`, `2days 3hours`, etc.\n\n## Architecture\n\nThe export command is a **read-only, offline operation** — no network, no Client, no transport. It opens `Storage` directly, queries the outbox, encodes each message as a `WirePayload` frame, and writes through `BundleWriter`.\n\n### File layout\n\n- `apps/client/src/export.rs` — self-contained export logic, called from `main.rs` export arm\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- `reme-storage` — `Storage::open()`, `OutboxStore` trait\n- `reme-outbox` — `PendingMessage`, `OutboxStore` trait\n- `reme-message` — `WirePayload::Message`, `OuterEnvelope`, postcard decoding\n- `reme-bundle` — `BundleWriter`\n- `reme-identity` — `PublicID` parsing for `--to`\n- `humantime` — `--since` duration parsing (zero-dep crate)\n\n## Data Flow\n\n1. Open `Storage::open(data_dir/messages.db)` — read-only access\n2. If `--to` provided: parse base64 into `PublicID`, call `storage.outbox_get_for_recipient(pubid)`\n3. Otherwise: call `storage.outbox_get_pending()`\n4. If `--include-sent`: use `storage.outbox_get_all()` (or `outbox_get_all_for_recipient()`) instead — a new method that includes confirmed entries\n5. Apply in-memory filters in order:\n   - `--since`: filter where `created_at_ms >= now - duration`\n   - `--limit`: take first N entries (oldest first)\n6. For each `PendingMessage`:\n   - Deserialize: `postcard::from_bytes::<OuterEnvelope>(&msg.envelope_bytes)`\n   - Wrap: `WirePayload::Message(envelope)`\n   - Encode: `wire_payload.encode()` → frame bytes\n7. Check output path: error if file exists and `--force` not set\n8. Write bundle: `BundleWriter::new(File::create(path))` → `write_frame()` per message → `finish()`\n9. Print summary to stderr: `Exported N messages to <file>`\n\n## Storage Layer Changes\n\n### New `OutboxStore` methods\n\n```rust\n/// Returns all outbox entries including confirmed and expired.\nfn outbox_get_all(&self) -> Result<Vec<PendingMessage>, OutboxError>;\n\n/// Returns all outbox entries for a recipient including confirmed and expired.\nfn outbox_get_all_for_recipient(&self, recipient: &PublicID) -> Result<Vec<PendingMessage>, OutboxError>;\n```\n\nThese mirror `outbox_get_pending()` and `outbox_get_for_recipient()` but without the confirmed/expired filter in the WHERE clause.\n\n## Edge Cases\n\n- No matching messages → print \"Nothing to export\" to stderr, exit 0\n- File exists without `--force` → error with message suggesting `--force`\n- Invalid `--to` pubid → error: \"Invalid public ID: expected 44-character base64\"\n- Corrupt `envelope_bytes` in DB → skip with warning, continue export\n- Empty outbox → valid empty bundle (0 frames), print \"Nothing to export\"\n\n## Tombstones\n\n**Skipped for v0.5.** Tombstones are fire-and-forget via transport, not queued in the outbox. The `pending_acks` table stores ack secrets for future retry but reconstructing `SignedAckTombstone` requires recipient context and re-signing. Will revisit when tombstone retry is implemented.\n\n## Testing\n\n- **Unit tests** (in `export.rs`): export with in-memory Storage, verify bundle round-trips via `BundleReader`\n- **Filter tests**: `--to` filters correctly, `--since` excludes old messages, `--limit` caps output, combinations work\n- **Integration test**: create messages via `Client`, run export, read back with `BundleReader`, verify frames match original envelopes\n- **Edge case tests**: empty outbox produces valid empty bundle, corrupt envelope skipped with warning\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- Tombstone export (see above)\n- Compression (postcard encoding is already compact)\n- Bundle encryption (envelopes are already E2E encrypted)\n- Streaming/incremental export (premature optimization)\n- Marking exported messages (export is non-destructive, no state changes)\n",
