tes. The explicit `has_message` check exists only to count duplicates separately in the summary. This is fine for UX but adds a round-trip per message. For large imports, this could be slow. Consider noting this as a known trade-off.\n\n---\n\n### Suggestions (Nice to Have)\n\n**5. Export with `--force` and empty results deletes the file but still creates it if non-empty existed before**\n\nIn `export.rs` lines 41-47: when `envelopes.is_empty()` and `args.force` is true, the existing file is removed. But if `envelopes.is_empty()` and `args.force` is false, the function just prints \"Nothing to export\" and returns `Ok(())`, leaving the existing file untouched. This is fine. However, note that if `--force` is not set and the file does not exist, the empty-export path still returns `Ok(())` without creating anything -- consistent behavior.\n\n**6. `_config` parameter in both `run_export` and `run_import`**\n\nBoth functions accept `_config: &NodeConfig` but never use it. If this is reserved for future use (e.g., node identity for signed exports), an explicit comment would clarify intent. Otherwise, remove the dead parameter.\n\n**7. Export `--since` should accept ISO 8601 timestamps too**\n\nCurrently only duration strings like \"24h\" and \"7d\" are accepted via `humantime`. For operational use, absolute timestamps (\"2026-03-27T00:00:00Z\") would also be useful. Low priority.\n\n**8. No tests for the new code**\n\nThere are no unit or integration tests for:\n- `export_messages` query logic (different filter combinations)\n- `run_export` (end-to-end: store messages, export, verify bundle)\n- `run_import` (end-to-end: import bundle, verify stored messages, tombstone handling)\n- `parse_routing_key` edge cases\n- `parse_since` edge cases\n- The `Cli` / `Commands` parsing behavior (subcommand defaults)\n\nGiven this is prototype-stage, this is understandable, but these are the highest-value tests to add before merging.\n\n**9. `open_store` calls `std::process::exit(1)` on failure**\n\nThe `open_store` function in `main.rs` (line 166) calls `process::exit(1)` on error. This is fine for a top-level binary helper, but it makes the function unusable in test contexts. If you plan to test export/import end-to-end, consider returning a `Result` instead.\n\n---\n\n### Security Assessment\n\n- **SQL injection**: Not a concern. The dynamic query in `export_messages` uses numbered bind parameters (`?1`, `?2`, `?3`) for all user-influenced values. The `LIMIT` value is a `usize` (cannot contain SQL). No string concatenation of user input into SQL.\n- **Tombstone verification**: Import correctly verifies `ack_secret` against stored `ack_hash` using constant-time comparison before deleting. Cannot be used to delete arbitrary messages.\n- **File overwrite protection**: Export checks `args.file.exists() && !args.force` before writing. Correct.\n- **Path traversal**: Both export and import accept file paths from CLI args. This is expected for a CLI tool and not a concern (the operator already has shell access).\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nThe implementation is solid and well-structured for a first pass. The main concern is the backward compatibility break for bare `reme-node` invocations with serve-specific flags (issue #1). The lack of tests (issue #8) is the second priority. Everything else is minor cleanup. No security vulnerabilities found.\n\n### Files Reviewed\n\n- `/home/leon0399/Projects/reme/.claude/worktrees/feat-186-node-subcommands/apps/node/src/config.rs`\n- `/home/leon0399/Projects/reme/.claude/worktrees/feat-186-node-subcommands/apps/node/src/main.rs`\n- `/home/leon0399/Projects/reme/.claude/worktrees/feat-186-node-subcommands/apps/node/src/export.rs`\n- `/home/leon0399/Projects/reme/.claude/worktrees/feat-186-node-subcommands/apps/node/src/import.rs`\n- `/home/leon0399/Projects/reme/.claude/worktrees/feat-186-node-subcommands/crates/reme-node-core/src/mailbox_store.rs`\n- `/home/leon0399/Projects/reme/.claude/worktrees/feat-186-node-subcommands/apps/node/Cargo.toml`</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>45842</total_tokens><tool_uses>19</tool_uses><duration_ms>236389</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: /tmp/claude-1000/-home-leon0399-Projects-reme/03f30216-bf11-4896-ba61-28ed420ab886/tasks/a365ae2416215f48b.output",
