ready exist — no need to add more\n\n## Existing Code Context\n\nThe crate already has these types (in `src/types.rs`):\n```rust\npub struct RawDiscoveredPeer { instance_name, addresses, port, txt_records, discovered_at }\npub enum DiscoveryEvent { PeerDiscovered(RawDiscoveredPeer), PeerUpdated(RawDiscoveredPeer), PeerLost(String) }\npub enum DiscoveryError { BindFailed(String), AlreadyAdvertising, NotAdvertising, BackendError(String) }\npub const DEFAULT_SERVICE_TYPE: &str = \"_reme._tcp.local.\";\n```\n\nAnd the trait (in `src/backend.rs`):\n```rust\n#[async_trait]\npub trait DiscoveryBackend: Send + Sync {\n    async fn start_advertising(&mut self, spec: AdvertisementSpec) -> Result<(), DiscoveryError>;\n    async fn stop_advertising(&mut self) -> Result<(), DiscoveryError>;\n    fn subscribe(&self) -> mpsc::Receiver<DiscoveryEvent>;\n    async fn shutdown(&mut self) -> Result<(), DiscoveryError>;\n}\n```\n\nThe crate uses workspace deps: `async-trait`, `tokio` (sync feature), `thiserror`, `hex`, `tracing`.\n\n## Branch Setup\n\nYou MUST work from `feat/target-capabilities` branch which has the latest code. Create a new branch `feat/discovery-backends` based on it.\n\n```bash\ngit switch feat/target-capabilities\ngit switch -c feat/discovery-backends\n```\n\n## After Implementation\n\n1. Run `cargo test -p reme-discovery` and `cargo clippy -p reme-discovery --all-features -- -D warnings` and `cargo fmt --all -- --check`\n2. Invoke the `simplify` skill to review and clean up your changes\n3. Commit with a clear message\n4. Push and create a PR with `gh pr create --base feat/lan-discovery`\n5. Wait for CI: run `gh pr checks <PR_NUMBER>` in a loop (check every 30s, max 10 attempts)\n6. If CI fails, fix and push again\n7. When CI passes, send a message to `reviewer` asking for code review\n8. Wait for reviewer feedback. If changes requested, fix them, push, re-check CI, and ask for re-review\n9. When approved, send a message to the team lead reporting completion with