            "content": "# mDNS Privacy: Replace hostname+PID instance name\n\n**Issue:** #108\n**Date:** 2026-03-26\n**Status:** Design\n\n## Problem\n\n`crates/reme-discovery/src/mdns_sd.rs:156-169` leaks the machine hostname and process ID in two places:\n\n```rust\nlet hostname = hostname::get()...;\nlet instance_name = format!(\"{hostname}-{}\", std::process::id());\nlet host_fqdn = format!(\"{hostname}.local.\");\n```\n\nAny mDNS browser on the LAN sees the hostname (e.g. `leos-macbook`) and PID. This violates reme's privacy-by-design principle — the advertised name should reveal no information beyond what's already in the TXT records.\n\n## Design\n\n### Instance name\n\nReplace `{hostname}-{pid}` with `reme-{hex(routing_key)}`:\n\n```rust\nlet instance_name = format!(\"reme-{}\", hex::encode(routing_key));\n// e.g. \"reme-deadbeef0123456789abcdeffedcba98\"\n```\n\n- 37 chars — well within the 63-byte DNS label limit\n- The routing key is already broadcast in cleartext in the TXT `rk` field, so this leaks no additional information\n- Stable across restarts (same identity = same name) — avoids spurious peer-lost/peer-discovered churn in the discovery controller\n- Unique per identity (routing key is a truncated BLAKE3 hash)\n\n### Host FQDN\n\nReplace `{hostname}.local.` with `reme-{hex(routing_key)}.local.`:\n\n```rust\nlet host_fqdn = format!(\"reme-{}.local.\", hex::encode(routing_key));\n```\n\nSame rationale — the hostname in the A/AAAA record target is visible on the wire.\n\n### API change: `AdvertisementSpec`\n\nAdd a typed `routing_key` field to `AdvertisementSpec` so the mDNS backend can derive the instance name without parsing TXT records:\n\n```rust\npub struct AdvertisementSpec {\n    pub service_type: String,\n    pub port: u16,\n    pub txt_records: HashMap<String, String>,\n    pub routing_key: Option<RoutingKey>,  // NEW\n}\n```\n\n`Option` because:\n- The `DiscoveryBackend` trait is generic — non-mDNS backends or test code might not have a routing key\n- When `None`, the mDNS backend falls back to `reme-{random}` (e.g. hex-encoded random 16 bytes) for forward compatibility\n\n`AdvertisementSpec::new()` initializes `routing_key: None`. The client caller already has the routing key and sets it explicitly.\n\n### Caller change\n\n`apps/client/src/discovery/mod.rs:119-124`:\n\n```rust\nlet our_rk: [u8; 16] = identity.public_id().routing_key().into();\nlet txt = reme_discovery::encode_txt(&our_rk, port);\nlet spec = reme_discovery::AdvertisementSpec {\n    txt_records: txt,\n    routing_key: Some(our_rk),  // NEW\n    ..reme_discovery::AdvertisementSpec::new(port)\n};\n```\n\n### Fallback when routing_key is None\n\nFor test code and future backends that don't provide a routing key:\n\n```rust\nlet instance_name = match &spec.routing_key {\n    Some(rk) => format!(\"reme-{}\", hex::encode(rk)),\n    None => format!(\"reme-{:032x}\", rand::random::<u128>()),\n};\n```\n\nThe fallback uses 32 hex chars of randomness — same length as a routing key, unique per session.\n\n### hostname crate removal\n\nAfter this change, the `hostname` crate is no longer needed by `reme-discovery`. Remove it from `Cargo.toml` if no other code in the crate uses it.\n\n## Files changed\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `crates/reme-discovery/src/types.rs` | Add `routing_key: Option<RoutingKey>` to `AdvertisementSpec`, update `new()` |\n| `crates/reme-discovery/src/mdns_sd.rs` | Derive instance name and host FQDN from routing key instead of hostname+PID |\n| `crates/reme-discovery/Cargo.toml` | Remove `hostname` dep, add `rand` if not already present |\n| `apps/client/src/discovery/mod.rs` | Pass `routing_key: Some(our_rk)` in `AdvertisementSpec` |\n| `crates/reme-discovery/src/fake.rs` | Update test `AdvertisementSpec` construction if needed (just add `routing_key: None`) |\n\n## What this does NOT change\n\n- TXT record format (unchanged)\n- Discovery controller logic (instance name is still an opaque string key)\n- `DiscoveryBackend` trait (unchanged — `AdvertisementSpec` is the input, not the trait)\n- Wire protocol (no wire format changes)\n\n## Testing\n\n- Existing mDNS tests continue to pass (they use `AdvertisementSpec::new()` which defaults to `routing_key: None`)\n- Verify instance name format in `start_advertising` with both `Some(rk)` and `None` cases\n- `cargo clippy`, `cargo fmt`, `cargo test --workspace`\n",
